com.paypal.merchant.sdk.domain
Interface SecureCreditCard

All Known Subinterfaces:
ManualEntryCardData
public interface SecureCreditCard

Sets of card data that move in/out of the SDK must implement this interface. The CardReaderManager will send up an object that implements SecureCreditCard when it detects a card swipe. Also, when taking a payment you can supply an object that implements SecureCreditCard (like the domain.ManualEntryCardData object, the SecureCreditCard object that CardReaderManager emitted during a swipe, or your own credit card object that implements SecureCreditCard).

isSignatureRequired

boolean isSignatureRequired()
Returns a boolean to indicate whether a signature is required or not in order to complete the transaction. NOTE: this is used mainly in case of EMV flow where the chip on the card and terminal decide whether a customer signature is required or not and the app is expected honor the same.

Returns:
: a boolean value indicating whether the customer signature is required or not.
